00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,000
Skiing.

564
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:54,920
Skydiving.

565
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,160
Diving.

566
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:58,640
Okay, okay.
Rock climbing.

567
00:30:58,707 --> 00:30:59,719
Okay, okay.

568
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:01,520
So, what do you have left to accomplish?

569
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:05,480
My next plan

570
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:07,280
is to do all those things
in the country.

571
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,160
I'm going to do bungee jumping

572
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:10,320
at Shiyan.

573
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,240
In a sense,

574
00:31:13,240 --> 00:31:14,877
jumping off in that way

575
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:17,360
is probably the closest
you can get to ascending.

576
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:21,320
I envy you.

577
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,600
Well, this is how rich kids are.

578
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,637
It's such a deadly thing,

579
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,400
but you sounded like it's aspiring.

580
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:32,680
You envy me, and I envy you too.

581
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,720
Why do you envy me?

582
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,120
I'm the only child in my family.

583
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:42,720
Countless pairs of eyes in my family

584
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,117
keep staring at me

585
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,480
from the moment I was born.

586
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:47,877
They are afraid that
something will happen to me

587
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:48,880
if I'm not being careful.

588
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:58,880
But I do feel for them.

589
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:01,840
And I understand them now.

590
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:04,680
The way you enjoy the games

591
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:07,600
might really cost your life.

592
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,480
That is why

593
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:15,200
having parents is good,

594
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:17,240
but not having parents
is not as miserable as you say.

595
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:19,240
My life belongs to my family.

596
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,480
Your life belongs to you.

597
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:23,880
How nice it is.

598
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:31,320
Come, let's play for another two rounds.

599
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:40,517
You reminded me just now.

600
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,000
I was rootless before.

601
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,080
But I have it now.

602
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:47,240
I am the successor of
the Jiang family's acupuncture sect.

603
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,320
If something happens to me,

604
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:51,117
the acupuncture sect will be over.

605
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,877
So, my life is very precious now.

606
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,920
I want to cherish it.

607
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:56,637
I can't care much about your sect.

608
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:58,240
But I want to protect my sect.

609
00:32:59,120 --> 00:32:59,920
Just you go.

610
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:01,400
Okay.

611
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:04,760
Successor, you must protect yourself.

612
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:09,080
Take it easy!

613
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:10,480
Don't worry.

614
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:43,960
This is not the way to go back home.

615
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:47,320
The most important trip
hasn't started yet.

616
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:49,280
We're not going back yet?

617
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:50,437
We have to go back now.

618
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,077
I still haven't do
the calligraphy exercise.

619
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,397
If your dad checks my homework tonight,

620
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,840
I'm sure I'll be dead.

621
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:56,000
There's enough time to do it.

622
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:57,880
There's not enough time to do it!

623
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:19,120
What are you going to buy at this place?

624
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:21,200
You'll find out later.

625
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:27,360
Mr. Ren.

626
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:28,400
I haven't seen you for a long time.

627
00:34:29,160 --> 00:34:30,640
What good things did you bring today?

628
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:33,680
Take a look.

629
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,437
You know
if this thing I wore is real or fake.

630
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:39,360
And you know
the price of the good agarwood now.

631
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:41,680
I can say
there is no price for this piece.

632
00:34:43,560 --> 00:34:44,760
It's a good stuff.

633
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:46,680
But it has your birth date on it.

634
00:34:46,764 --> 00:34:48,077
You also know

635
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:50,440
those who wear agarwood pendants
are for own or family protection.

636
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:51,680
Not very good to offer.

637
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:52,800
Quote a price.

638
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:54,160
How about this?

639
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:55,580
One time offer.
One hundred thousand.

640
00:34:55,767 --> 00:34:57,000
One hundred...

641
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:58,360
One hundred thousand?

642
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:03,758
What is this

643
00:35:03,841 --> 00:35:05,240
that costs one hundred thousand?

644
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:07,077
I didn't know you were wearing

645
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:08,440
such an expensive thing.

646
00:35:08,700 --> 00:35:09,837
Deal.

647
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,386
Okay.

648
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,560
How much is your watch?

649
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:18,480
Let me see.

650
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:19,920
The watch...
Watch...

651
00:35:20,004 --> 00:35:21,318
What are you doing?

652
00:35:21,401 --> 00:35:22,877
I'm checking
what other valuable things you have.

653
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:24,277
-Don't touch me.
-Take it out.

654
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:25,677
Let's keep a distance. Man and
woman shouldn't touch each other.

655
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:26,560
Take it out.

656
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:32,600
You lost it?

657
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:33,600
You lost it?

658
00:35:37,480 --> 00:35:39,800
Is it something that can be lost?

659
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:41,240
Think about it.

660
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:43,680
Did you leave it in the library?

661
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:45,960
That's right.
I'll call Head Librarian Wang

662
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:47,080
and ask him to find it.

663
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:48,280
Mom, no need for that.

664
00:35:48,364 --> 00:35:50,280
It's the festive season.
He is celebrating with his family too.

665
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,957
Let's call him
after the festive season, okay?

666
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,360
That's not okay.

667
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:54,900
It's such an important stuff.

668
00:35:54,984 --> 00:35:56,038
I'll call him.

669
00:35:56,121 --> 00:35:58,077
Mom, don't bother about this.
Don't need to call him.

670
00:35:58,173 --> 00:35:59,533
Go and find it at the library.

671
00:35:59,617 --> 00:36:00,993
Don't make your grandma worry.

672
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,880
Maybe it's not in the library.

673
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:08,477
Moreover, you gave me this.

674
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,680
It's not that I want to wear it.

675
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:11,080
Why blame me when I lost it?

676
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:13,877
Moreover, the string doesn't know that
the pendant is expensive.

677
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,317
I couldn't help it either

678
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:16,200
since the string broke.

679
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:17,920
This isn't the first time though.

680
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:20,240
The string has broken?

681
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:22,680
That's true.

682
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:25,040
I changed twice before.

683
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:26,240
It's all my fault.

684
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:27,797
I haven't changed it for a long time.

685
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:29,640
Mom, how can we blame you?

686
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,440
Hundreds of thousands are gone.

687
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:38,600
Hundreds of thousands?

688
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,440
It's been so long.

689
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:44,440
The pendant should be valuable now.

690
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,000
Head Librarian Wang.

691
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,440
Yes, yes. It's me.

692
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,720
I'd like to ask you something.

693
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:03,197
What a guy.

694
00:37:03,280 --> 00:37:05,560
It's so expensive. If I had known
about it, I would have brought it back.

695
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:07,280
What did you say?

696
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:11,640
You would have brought it back?

697
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,080
No.

698
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:16,720
I mean,

699
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:18,480
I should have

700
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:21,397
searched properly in the library

701
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:22,720
since it's expensive stuff.

702
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:51,960
What are you doing?

703
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,720
I'm making one for Tian Zhen.

704
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,440
Our grandchildren
will have his own blessings.

705
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,717
He doesn't take that thing seriously,

706
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:02,797
so don't bother yourself with this.

707
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:03,680
Never mind.

708
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:05,000
That can't be.

709
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:08,197
He is the only child in our family.

710
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,280
We have to protect him.

711
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,280
I've lost count of it.

712
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:15,200
Since he was young,

713
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:18,320
I wonder why

714
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:21,160
those things that I gave him

715
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,400
all didn't last long.

716
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:24,600
Either he lost it

717
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:26,000
or someone stole it.

718
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,480
If this continues,

719
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,080
what should we do?

720
00:38:29,360 --> 00:38:30,680
We'll do what we should do.

721
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:32,200
Since he was young,

722
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:34,400
he lost a lot of the amulets.

723
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:36,760
Yet he grew up safely.

724
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,437
We are old now.

725
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:43,997
We'll just keep these things with us.

726
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:45,320
Don't do it for him.

727
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:46,920
I know.

728
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:49,320
The pendant that he lost this time,

729
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:51,000
we must get it back.

730
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:53,160
But

731
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:55,120
my mom told me before.

732
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:57,280
The son of a prestigious family
has a short life.

733
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,600
He'll need something to suppress it.

734
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:07,560
It's getting more expensive.

735
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:30,720
Why are you here?

736
00:39:33,633 --> 00:39:34,717
Sun Tou Tou.

737
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:35,966
I'm...

738
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,080
I'm sitting here for a while.

739
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,040
You two have made a deal, right?

740
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:52,520
Professor Song.

741
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:53,960
I'm sorry I'm late.

742
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,520
How much did you pay for my son's stuff?

743
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:58,360
One hundred thousand.

744
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:00,320
One...

745
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:02,840
You know about it?

746
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:09,680
What does this mean?

747
00:40:15,120 --> 00:40:15,920
You've sold it?

748
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:18,720
We have always been doing this.

749
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:20,560
He comes to sell stuff
and I come to redeem it.

750
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,200
Why did you sell it?

751
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,880
Yesterday, I went out for a drink.

752
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,477
I left the store to my staff.

753
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:28,798
He accidentally... He...

754
00:40:28,881 --> 00:40:30,840
I think you don't want
to do our business anymore.

755
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,800
Do you know this is called
embezzlement of assets?

756
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:35,277
It's hard for me too.

757
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:37,797
I've scolded him all morning.

758
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:39,185
-I...
-Who did he sell it to?

759
00:40:39,269 --> 00:40:40,676
Go and find that person.

760
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,997
The thing is

761
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:43,357
I don't know who he sold to.

762
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:44,612
He is not a regular customer.

763
00:40:48,580 --> 00:40:49,872
What about your surveillance camera?

764
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,200
It's already broken.

765
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,459
It's just decoration.

766
